  ── ARCHITECTURAL FINDINGS ─────────────────────────────────────────
  1. BIAS_LUT: requires population from Test 9 calibration data.
     Until calibrated, mode 001 = mode 000 arithmetically.

  2. PRE-SCALED: reduces accumulator magnitude (result-domain floor
     collapse unchanged — exponent underflow occurs before decoder).
     Effective mitigation for W03/W06 accumulator saturation paths.

  3. SAFE-ACCUM: 32-bit modular overflow protection is sound but
     not exercisable within 63-MAC tile windows (peak ≈ 516K ≪ 2^32).
     Correct design; effectiveness observable only in very long
     accumulation runs or with very high-magnitude codewords.

  4. DEPTH-MONITOR: fires for max_depth ≤ FILL_CYCLES (≤6 with
     FILL_CYCLES=6).  Provides measurable automatic reset control.
     Optimal window: max_depth=4 (tightest firing threshold).

  5. SCHEDULER: bounded depth windows prevent floor attractor onset;
     advantage maximised in mixed-regime (deep-chain + cancel) loads.
